cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is about a learning-based approach for color enhancement, which is a common task in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning (DRL) method, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a Markov Decision Process (MDP) also suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves global color adjustment operations, which could be related to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
